I"	<ol>
  <li>Peel the onions and garlic</li>
  <li>Blend or chop the onions and garlic</li>
  <li>Rinse and blend or chop tomato</li>
  <li>Pour olive oil into pan. Cover 1/3 of the pan</li>
  <li>Bring the stove to medium high heat</li>
  <li>Sautee the onions and garlic until golden/light brown</li>
  <li>Pour the tomato sauce into the pan</li>
  <li>Bring the stove to medium low heat</li>
  <li>Put the sugar, salt, chopped tomato, pepper, onion powder, garic powder, oregano, and parsley into the pan</li>
  <li>Put one spoonful of tomato paste into pan</li>
  <li>Put two spoonful of diced tomatoes into the pan</li>
  <li>Pour the water into the pan</li>
  <li>Stir for 5 minutes while it is boiling (do not let boil over)</li>
  <li>Bring the stove down to low</li>
  <li>Stir, for 20 seconds, every 5 minutes for the first 30. Do not worry if it does not taste right for the first 2 hours, the longer it cooks the more the ingredients mix</li>
  <li>Stir, for 20 seconds, every 10-15 minutes for the next 3 hours</li>
</ol>
